  "prompt": "How do I buy a share of the Green Bay Packers' stock?",
  "response": "The Green Bay Packers are unique in the NFL as they are publicly owned and have conducted stock sales to allow fans and supporters to become shareholders. However, these shares are not like typical corporate stocks, as they do not pay dividends and cannot be traded.\n\nHere\u2019s how you can potentially purchase a share if and when they are available:\n\n1. **Check Availability**: The Packers only sell their stock during specific offering periods. The last sale was in 2021. To find out if a new sale is occurring, check the official Green Bay Packers website or sign up for their newsletter to receive notifications.\n\n2. **Visit Official Channels**: When an offering is active, purchases can typically be made through the official Green Bay Packers website. Avoid third-party sites, as shares must be bought directly from the Packers.\n\n3. **Understand the Terms**: Packers shares are more like memorabilia than traditional stock. They have no resale value, voting rights are limited, and they do not appreciate in value.\n\n4. **Purchase**: During an offering, you can buy shares through the team\u2019s official website. You might need to create an account or provide personal information such as your address and payment details.\n\n5. **Follow Up**: After purchasing, you\u2019ll receive a certificate recognizing your ownership. This can be a prized possession for many fans.\n\nRemember, owning a share in the Green Bay Packers is more about being part of the team\u2019s history and supporting community-driven ownership rather than making a financial investment. Keep an eye on their official communications for any announcements of new stock sales.",
